column5: I fished off the Islands at Sturgeon today, 43 fow, landed 8 wallys (kept4), 10 nice perch & 1 herring.  Beauty day, no coat all afternoon.  3 - 4" of water on the ride back to shore.  Gonna get worse with mild temps this week.

Great stuff Brian! I wish we could have met up on saturday morning but it was nasty weather at 630am. I got called to work in the late morning so in the end, I was better off. Enjoy your walleye filets. Did you keep mr. Herring?
Herring is still swimming.  One of the locals tell me they R wormy.  3 -4" of water on the ice when I returned at 6:30.  With mild temps it's going to deterriorate quickly.  Play safe guys!!
